## Architecture (stage progression)

| Concept | Location | Notes |
|---------|----------|-------|
| Shape roster | `GAME_SHAPES` in `src/constants/game.ts` | Fixed list; index = `shapeIndex` |
| Pool tiers | `POOL_TIER_CORE`, `_MID`, `_ADVANCED` in `game.ts` | Indices into `GAME_SHAPES` |
| Active pool | `getActivePool(level)` in `useCandyBreak.ts` | Level 1–2: core; 3–4: core+mid; 5+: all tiers |
| Stage count | `getStageCountForLevel(level)` | Target 5 / 7 / 8–10; capped by pool size |
| Level shuffle | `sampleStageOrder(pool, count)` | Fisher-Yates subset, then order shuffle |
| New level | `createNewLevelState(level)` | `sampleStageOrder(getActivePool(level), count)` + `stageSlot = 0` |
| Runtime state | `stageOrder`, `stageSlot` in `useCandyBreak.ts` | `shapeIndex = stageOrder[stageSlot]` (derived) |
| Advance stage | `stageSlot + 1` | Last slot → next level → new pool sample + shuffle |
| Save / resume | `ISavedGame.stageOrder`, `stageSlot` | Pool re-derived from `level` only for **new** levels; resume keeps saved `stageOrder` |
| Stars | `stars_L${level}_S${shapeIndex}` | Unchanged — keyed by shape, not slot |

**Helpers:** `shuffleIndices`, `getActivePool`, `getStageCountForLevel`, `sampleStageOrder`, `createSequentialStageOrder`, `createNewLevelState`, `resolveStageFromSave`

**Files:** `src/constants/game.ts`, `src/hooks/useCandyBreak.ts`

### Pool tiers (`GAME_SHAPES` indices)

| Tier | Constant | Styles | Indices |
|------|----------|--------|---------|
| Core | `POOL_TIER_CORE` | `classic`, `color-target`, `locked-tiles`, `bomb-storm` | 0, 1, 2, 4 |
| Mid | `POOL_TIER_MID` | `timer-attack`, `move-saver`, `pure-match` | 5, 8, 9 |
| Advanced | `POOL_TIER_ADVANCED` | `multiplier-rush`, `order-collect`, `combo-goal` | 3, 6, 7 |

### Stages per level

| Level | Pool | Target stages | Actual (current roster) |
|-------|------|---------------|-------------------------|
| 1–2 | Core | 5 | **4** (core pool has 4 modes) |
| 3–4 | Core + Mid | 7 | 7 |
| 5 | All tiers | 8–10 (random) | 8–10 |

## Architecture (i18n)

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Types | `src/i18n/types.ts` | `Language`, `IStrings`, banner keys |
| Strings | `src/i18n/translations.ts` | ko/en copy for all UI text |
| Format | `src/i18n/format.ts` | `{placeholder}` interpolation |
| Context | `src/i18n/I18nContext.tsx` | `I18nProvider`, `useI18n`, AsyncStorage `appLanguage` |
| Toggle | `src/components/LanguageToggle.tsx` | KO/EN switch (intro screen only) |

- Language choice persists in `AsyncStorage` key `appLanguage` (`ko` | `en`, default `ko`)
- `App.tsx` wraps content in `I18nProvider`; intro sets language, game screens read it
- Add new UI strings to **both** `ko` and `en` in `translations.ts`; use `format()` for dynamic values

## Shipped fixes

### Level-gated active pool (step 6)

Each level samples a **subset** of modes from a level-appropriate pool, then shuffles play order.

- `getActivePool(level)` — which shape indices are eligible
- `getStageCountForLevel(level)` — how many to pick (capped at pool size)
- `sampleStageOrder(pool, count)` — random subset + shuffle
- `createNewLevelState` uses pool logic automatically on new game and level advance
- No score gate; no mode-select UI; no extra save field

**Files:** `src/constants/game.ts`, `useCandyBreak.ts`

### Random mode order per level (step 5)

- `stageOrder: number[]`, `stageSlot: number`, derived `shapeIndex`
- Persisted in `ISavedGame`; old saves migrate via `resolveStageFromSave`
- Stars key unchanged: `stars_L${level}_S${shapeIndex}`

**Files:** `useCandyBreak.ts`

### Bomb / lightning flash

`bombActivating: IPosition | null` — UI treats a cell as bomb if `bombPosition` **or** `bombActivating` matches.

**Files:** `useCandyBreak.ts`, `App.tsx`

### Immediate goal update

`goalRemaining` updates per cascade step via `computeGoalAfterSteps`, not only in `finalizeMove`.

**Files:** `useCandyBreak.ts`

### Game Over overlay

- Full-board dim + card panel for readable text
- Tap overlay → `restart()` (retry stage) or `restartFromLevelOne()` (full win)

**Files:** `App.tsx`

### Locked-tiles touch

- Frozen cells use `Pressable`; tapping frozen no longer clears adjacent selection

**Files:** `App.tsx`, `useCandyBreak.ts`

## Step 7 — next: Tier B modes (Level 4+ only)

Add after Step 6 so new modes do not bloat early levels.

**Candidates:** `jelly-tiles`, `stone-blocks`, `special-hunt`  
**Tier C (later):** `color-flood`, `ice-spread`, `mystery`

When adding a Tier B mode:

1. Append to `GAME_SHAPES` + add `POOL_TIER_B` constant in `game.ts`
2. Include `POOL_TIER_B` in `getActivePool` for level ≥ 4 (or level 5 only — decide at implementation)
3. Follow per-mode checklist in candy-break rule (`types`, `game.ts`, hook, `App.tsx`, i18n)

